        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Glycogen storage disease (GSD) due to liver phosphorylase kinase (PhK) deficiency is a benign inborn error of glycogen metabolism characterized by hepatomegaly growth retardation and mild delay in motor development during childhood."
        },
